Chess legend Bobby Fischer, known for his maverick behavior and criticism of the US, faces 10 years in prison for violating sanctions by playing in Yugoslavia in 1992.
Japan may deport him to the US, but Iceland granting him citizenship could prevent this.
Fischer's supporters argue he won't get a fair trial in the US due to controversial statements.
Iceland's parliament recently granted him citizenship, showing widespread support.
Fischer's saga reflects a battle for freedom of speech and thought, with supporters rallying behind him for his right to express himself.
